# Deno Task Management & Execution

## Task Configuration

### Deno.json Tasks

Tasks are defined in [deno.json](mdc:deno.json):

```json
{
  "tasks": {
    "dev": "deno run --allow-all --watch main.ts",
    "run": "deno run --allow-read --allow-env --allow-ffi --allow-run run.ts",
    "strapi": "deno task run strapi",
    "prismic": "deno task run prismic",
    "check": "deno check **/*.ts"
  }
}
```

### Task Execution Pattern

Use [run.ts](mdc:run.ts) for module routing:

```bash
deno task run strapi previewTemplatesCSV
deno task run prismic exportData
```

## Function Registry Pattern

### Main.ts Function Registry

Each module exports a function registry in [main.ts](mdc:strapi/main.ts):

```typescript
export const functions = {
  previewTemplatesCSV: () => formService.previewTemplatesCSV(),
  downloadPDFFromCSV: () => formService.downloadPDFFromCSV(),
  uploadFormFromCSV: () => formService.uploadFormFromCSV(),
  exportFormDataAsJSON: () => formService.exportFromDataAsJSON(),
  // ... other functions
};
```

### Function Configuration

Configure function behavior with metadata:

```typescript
export const functionConfigs: Record<string, { heavy?: boolean; media?: boolean }> = {
  previewTemplatesCSV: { heavy: true },
  genThumbnailImages: { media: true },
};
```

### CLI Interface

```typescript
if (import.meta.main) {
  const functionName = Deno.args[0];

  if (!functionName) {
    console.log("❌ No function name provided");
    console.log("📝 AVAILABLE FUNCTIONS:");
    Object.keys(functions).forEach((fn) => console.log(`  🦴 ${fn}`));
    Deno.exit(1);
  }

  const targetFunction = functions[functionName as keyof typeof functions];

  if (!targetFunction) {
    console.log(`❌ Function '${functionName}' not found`);
    console.log("💡 Did you mean one of these?");
    Object.keys(functions)
      .filter((fn) => fn.toLowerCase().includes(functionName.toLowerCase()))
      .forEach((fn) => console.log(`  🦴 ${fn}`));
    Deno.exit(1);
  }

  try {
    await load({ export: true });
    console.log(`🚀 Executing: ${functionName}`);
    logMemoryUsage("Before execution");
    await targetFunction();
    logMemoryUsage("After execution");
    console.log(`✅ Completed: ${functionName}`);
    Deno.exit(0);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error(`❌ Error executing '${functionName}':`, error);
    Deno.exit(1);
  }
}
```

## Permission Management

### Dynamic Permission Loading

[run.ts](mdc:run.ts) handles dynamic permissions based on function configuration:

```typescript
const permissions = ["--allow-net", "--allow-read", "--allow-write", "--allow-env"];
const v8Flags = [];

if (config.media) {
  permissions.push("--allow-ffi", "--allow-run");
}

if (config.heavy) {
  v8Flags.push("--v8-flags=--max-old-space-size=8192");
}
```

### Permission Categories

- **Basic**: `--allow-net`, `--allow-read`, `--allow-write`, `--allow-env`
- **Media**: `--allow-ffi`, `--allow-run` (for PDF processing)
- **Heavy**: `--v8-flags=--max-old-space-size=8192` (for large datasets)

## Environment Management

### Environment Loading

```typescript
import { load } from "@std/dotenv";

await load({ export: true });
```

### Environment Variables

Required environment variables:

- `STRAPI_ENDPOINT` - Strapi API endpoint
- `STRAPI_API_TOKEN` - Strapi API token
- `ENVIRONMENT` - Environment (production/staging)
- `GOOGLE_ACCESS_TOKEN` - Google Drive access token

## Import Map Configuration

### Deno.json Imports

```json
{
  "imports": {
    "@std/path": "jsr:@std/path@^1.0.6",
    "@std/dotenv": "jsr:@std/dotenv@^0.225.5",
    "@std/csv": "jsr:@std/csv@^1.0.6",
    "@strapi/": "./strapi/",
    "@prismic/": "./prismic/",
    "csv-writer": "npm:csv-writer@^1.6.0",
    "moment": "npm:moment@^2.30.1"
  }
}
```

### Import Patterns

- Use `@std/` for Deno standard library
- Use `@strapi/` for strapi module imports
- Use `@prismic/` for prismic module imports
- Use npm: prefix for npm packages

## Memory Management

### Memory Monitoring

```typescript
import { logMemoryUsage } from "./utils/helpers.ts";

logMemoryUsage("Before execution");
await performOperation();
logMemoryUsage("After execution");
```

### Memory Usage Pattern

```typescript
export function logMemoryUsage(label: string) {
  const usage = Deno.memoryUsage();
  console.log(`💾 Memory [${label}]:`);
  console.log(`   RSS: ${(usage.rss / 1024 / 1024).toFixed(2)} MB`);
  console.log(`   Heap Used: ${(usage.heapUsed / 1024 / 1024).toFixed(2)} MB`);
  console.log(`   Heap Total: ${(usage.heapTotal / 1024 / 1024).toFixed(2)} MB`);
}
```

## File System Operations

### Directory Creation

```typescript
await Deno.mkdir(directoryPath, { recursive: true });
```

### File Operations

```typescript
// Read file
const content = await Deno.readTextFile(filePath);

// Write file
await Deno.writeTextFile(filePath, content);

// Check file exists
try {
  const stat = await Deno.stat(filePath);
  return stat.isFile;
} catch {
  return false;
}
```

### Directory Iteration

```typescript
for await (const entry of Deno.readDir(directoryPath)) {
  if (entry.isFile && entry.name.endsWith(".pdf")) {
    // Process file
  }
}
```

## Error Handling and Exit Codes

### Exit Code Patterns

```typescript
// Success
Deno.exit(0);

// Error
Deno.exit(1);
```

### Error Handling in Main

```typescript
try {
  await targetFunction();
  Deno.exit(0);
} catch (error) {
  console.error(`❌ Error executing '${functionName}':`, error);
  Deno.exit(1);
}
```

